## 4. Sub-task breakdown (TZ-103.1 / 2 / 3)

**Execution ordering (explicit):**

```
TZ-103.1 (service decoupling)
      ↓
TZ-103.2 (lifecycle syncing)  ← depends on 103.1's `parentDestroyRef` config
      ↓
TZ-103.3 (CSS audit + RAF)    ← can run IN PARALLEL with 103.1 + 2 (independent file surface)
```

Rationale: TZ-103.2 consumers reference `parentDestroyRef?: DestroyRef` which TZ-103.1 introduces. Implementing 103.2 before 103.1 surfaces typecheck errors. TZ-103.3 touches `styles.css` (CSS only) and `pi-dialog.service.ts` (RAF repositioning hook) — both independent of 103.1/103.2 merchant surface; can ship in a parallel branch.

**Implementation strategy:** two branches — `branch-a` for 103.1+103.2 serial, `branch-b` for 103.3 — merge both into `main` once all 10 AC pass.

---

### TZ-103.1 — Service decoupling (closes #1, enables #4)

**Files:** `frontend/src/app/shared/ui/dialog/pi-dialog.service.ts` (only).

**Edits:**

```ts
// BEFORE (current fragment with bug):
private activeRef: OverlayRef | null = null;
private activeFocusTrap: ReturnType<ConfigurableFocusTrapFactory['create']> | null = null;
...
this.activeRef = overlayRef;
...
private cleanup() {
  if (this.activeFocusTrap) { /* destroy */ this.activeFocusTrap = null; }
  if (this.activeRef) { /* dispose */ this.activeRef = null; }
}

// AFTER (closure-bound per dialog):
open(component, config) {
  // overlayRef is LOCAL to this invocation; ref.close() captures it
  // via closure for safe per-dialog cleanup.
  const ref: DialogRef = {
    closed: computed(...),
    close: (v) => {
      if (isClosed()) return;
      closedSig.set(v); isClosed.set(true);
      // Dispose THIS dialog's overlay, not the service's singleton.
      focusTrap.destroy();
      overlayRef.dispose();
      // Also deregister from callers map (for TZ-103.2).
      if (config.parentDestroyRef) callersMap.delete(ref);
    },
  };
  ...
}
```

**Tests:** add developer-only `console.assert(overlayRef !== null)` patterns are removed in favour of unit tests: `pi-dialog.service.spec.ts` (NEW) asserting:

- (a) **N-cycle open-close** — opens 3 dialogs, closes middle one, closes outer two. Verifies all 3 overlays disposed (no leak). Currently the bug disposes 2 and leaks 1.
- (b) **`ref.close(false)` does NOT invoke `onDialogCloseOnce` callback** — disambiguates `filter(Boolean)` semantics.
- (c) **`parentDestroyRef` triggers `ref.close()` on caller destruction** — verifies TZ-103.2 lifecycle wiring works at unit level.
- (d) **Closing one dialog does NOT dispose sibling overlays** — explicit regression for the original Symptom #1 bug pattern.

### TZ-103.2 — Lifecycle syncing (closes #3)

**Files:** `pi-dialog.service.ts` (extends with callers Map + DestroyRef tracking); consumer pages (~10 sites).

**Service API addition:**

```ts
export interface DialogConfig<TResult, TData> {
  width?: ...;
  modal?: boolean;
  dismissOnBackdropClick?: boolean;
  dismissOnEscape?: boolean;
  data?: TData;
  ariaLabel?: string;
  /** NEW (TZ-103.2): caller's DestroyRef; service auto-closes dialog
      when the caller is destroyed (e.g. router tab-switch). */
  parentDestroyRef?: DestroyRef;
}
```

**Consumer wiring (10 sites):** in `texts.page.ts` openCreate/openEdit, `tables.page.ts` openCreate/openEdit/onDelete, `dictionaries.page.ts` onDelete, plus any other `dialog.open` consumers in `doc-constructor/builder/builder*.component.ts`:

```ts
// BEFORE:
const ref = this.dialog.open(TextBlockFormDialogComponent, { data: null, width: 'lg' });

// AFTER:
const ref = this.dialog.open(TextBlockFormDialogComponent, {
  data: null,
  width: 'lg',
  parentDestroyRef: this.destroyRef,    // TZ-103.2
});
```

`DestroyRef` is automatically injected via Angular 20's `inject(DestroyRef)`. Most pages already inject it (e.g., `builder.page.ts` does for `takeUntilDestroyed`).

### TZ-103.3 — CSS layout audit + first-mount positioning (closes #2)

**Files:** `frontend/src/styles.css` (verify import); `pi-dialog.service.ts` (add updatePosition in requestAnimationFrame).

**Verification steps pre-edit:**

1. `grep -nE 'cdk/overlay-prebuilt|pi-overlay-panel|pi-overlay-backdrop|pi-dialog-host-open' frontend/src/styles.css` — confirm imports and class definitions.
2. If `@import '@angular/cdk/overlay-prebuilt.css';` missing → add it at top of styles.css (above `@tailwind` directives to avoid cascade issues).
3. If `.pi-overlay-panel` defined but `display: block` (or equivalent layout-affecting class) not present → add minimal `display: block; min-width: 0;` rule.

**Service addition (handles racy first-mount layout):**

```ts
queueMicrotask(() => {
  // requestAnimationFrame lets Angular's first CD cycle + transitions commit
  // before CDK re-measures. Without this, the dialog may render at
  // coordinates computed against 0-width pane.
  requestAnimationFrame(() => {
    overlayRef.updatePosition();
    overlayRef.updateSize({ width: panelEl?.offsetWidth, height: panelEl?.offsetHeight });
  });
});
```

### TZ-103.4 (optional) — Consumer button hardening

If browser-use A/B testing reveals additional button issues after TZ-103.1+2+3, extend with: audit of `app-pi-button` host (`type="button"` confirmation in DOM); remove inline `type="submit"` if any button-by-mistake emits.

**Skip for now** — TZ-103.1+2+3 should fix symptom #4 organically.

