## 6. Acceptance criteria (testable)

| # | Criterion | Verification |
|---|---|---|
| AC-1 | Click `#cancel-button` in TextBlockFormDialog → dialog disappears in <300ms (accounts for the 180ms fade-in animation lifecycle in `pi-dialog.component.ts`) | browser-use click event + DOM check |
| AC-2 | Double-click `#create-button` via NATURAL user-input events (real click + ~100ms tick) → only 1 dialog opens; #cancel works | browser-use `click('#create-button'); tick(100); click('#create-button')` — NOT synthetic `dispatchEvent` (Angular zones coalesce synthetic events differently from real input; synthetic dispatch may not actually trigger the bug) |
| AC-3 | Open dialog on `/doc-constructor/texts` → navigate to `/materials` → no `.cdk-overlay-pane` exists in DOM after navigation | browser-use navigate + DOM count |
| AC-4 | First-mount dialog renders at exact viewport center on `/doc-constructor/texts` (no top-left); measured `left` and `top` both within ±20px of ideal | browser-use getBoundingClientRect |
| AC-5 | ESC key closes active dialog (long-standing behavior — confirm not regressed) | browser-use keydown |
| AC-6 | Backdrop click closes active dialog | browser-use click on overlay backdrop |
| AC-7 | Typecheck `pnpm exec tsc -p tsconfig.app.json --noEmit` exit 0 | CLI |
| AC-8 | No `console.error` events during 4-page smoke | browser-use sweep |
| AC-9 | `pi-dialog.service.spec.ts` passes; `dialog.open-open-close-close` doesn't leak | `pnpm jest <spec>` |
| AC-10 | Z-Order: opening `/materials` dialog (alerts) while `/doc-constructor/builder/:id` has 3-pane canvas open doesn't disrupt canvas | browser-use dual-dialog test |

