## 7. Cross-cutting concerns

### 7.1 Backwards compatibility for `DialogConfig`

`parentDestroyRef` is OPTIONAL. Existing callers that don't pass it retain current behaviour (no auto-close on caller destroy). Migration is opt-in.

### 7.2 No API break to `DialogRef`

`DialogRef.closed` signal + `ref.close(v)` contract unchanged. Consumers stay compatible.

### 7.3 `onDialogCloseOnce` re-entrancy safety

Stricter guard added: callback only fires if `toObservable` effect's host injector is alive at emit time. The current implementation already silently drops emissions when caller is destroyed (per JSDoc); we tighten to also check that `ref` is still alive (not disposed elsewhere).

### 7.4 Tab-switch UX expectation

Per current implementation, dialogs are expected to close automatically when tab-switched (orphaned modal dialogs over a new route are user-confusing). TZ-103.2 codifies this expectation. The acceptance criterion AC-3 enforces.

If a future use case needs persistent dialog across navigations (e.g. background-save «saving…» indicator), a separate config option `persistAcrossNavigation: true` would be added. Out of scope for TZ-103.

### 7.5 Focus trap isolation

After TZ-103.1, each `DialogRef` owns its `ConfigurableFocusTrap` instance. Cleanup (`focusTrap.destroy()`) inside the close closure. No cross-dialog leakage. AC-10 verifies.

### 7.6 CDK overlay CSS baseline (R-3 mitigation)

If `@angular/cdk/overlay-prebuilt.css` was missing, adding it could visually change other dialogs. **Concrete baseline capture protocol** (must run before AND after the CSS import edit):

1. **kit showcase baseline:** `/kit/overlays` — capture `pi-dialog` polymorphic shell (alert / form / content / destructive variants). 4 screenshots total.
2. **dictionaries baseline:** `/dictionaries` → click Удалить on existing unit row → AlertDialog (destructive variant). 1 screenshot.
3. **doc-constructor baseline:** `/doc-constructor/texts` → click Создать → TextBlockFormDialog (xl width, form variant, 2-column). 1 screenshot.
4. **dark-mode baseline (Chrome devtools toggle):** any of the above in dark mode = 6 additional screenshots.

Total: 12 baseline screenshots. **Diff against post-import screenshots** — any pixel-level difference outside the dialog itself (e.g. overlay backdrop tint, z-index changes) is unintended drift. Rollback if drift is real.

The baseline capture itself is ~5 screenshots via browser-use; the diff is PNG-hash or pixel-compare. Reuse tooling from TZ-86 evidence folder (`tasks/_archive/2026-07/TZ-103-css-baseline/`).

