## 10. Risk callouts (per thinker audit)

| # | Risk | Severity | Mitigation |
|---|---|---|---|
| R-1 | After TZ-103.1, if `cleanup()` disposes ONLY the local overlay, a previously-cached `global` "close-all" hack (if any exists) would fail | LOW | grep `pi-dialog.service.ts` for `closeAll`/`forceClose` — none today; verify after refactor |
| R-2 | `onDialogCloseOnce` re-entrancy: if the callback side-effect (e.g. `this.listRes.reload()`) tries to access a destroyed `listRes`, throws `NG0203 Injection context destroyed` | LOW | guard added in TZ-103.1 tighten; existing JSDoc already flags this pattern |
| R-3 | Adding `@angular/cdk/overlay-prebuilt.css` import could visually change other dialogs (kit pi-dialog showcase, alert variants) — subtle regression risk | LOW | capture baseline browser screenshots BEFORE applying CSS import; diff AFTER; rollback if diff is unintended drift |
| R-4 | The `parentDestroyRef` API is new; inconsistent adoption by consumers leaves some pages with broken #3 fix | MEDIUM | `grep -rn 'dialog\.open' frontend/src/app/pages --include='*.ts'` — count sites; verify each has `parentDestroyRef` before commit |
| R-5 | First-mount positioning tweak via `requestAnimationFrame` could fire BEFORE Angular's first CD cycle settles, making symptom #2 worse | LOW | use `queueMicrotask` + `requestAnimationFrame` chain (per code shape) — microtask runs after sync code, RAF runs after next paint |
| R-6 | If a future feature deliberately wants persistence across navigation (e.g. draft-save "saving..." indicator), TZ-103.2's auto-close would conflict | LOW | documented as future opt-in flag `persistAcrossNavigation` in §7.4 (out of TZ-103 scope) |
| R-7 | Tests not yet authored for `pi-dialog.service.ts` (no `*.spec.ts` exists today) — TZ-103.1 introduces the first | LOW | TZ-103.5 would add comprehensive coverage; TZ-103 ships with minimal N-cycle coverage (§5 item 2) |

